      "content": "i hear you on the consensus thing, but it feels like you're still framing it in a way that makes the protectionist view sound like an \"even if\" or a secondary thought. if a policy helps a whole community stay employed and secure, even if it makes some things slightly more expensive, isn't that a valid way to measure \"correctness\"? or is \"economic efficiency\" the only metric that actually matters to you?",
