      "content": "Tariffs are a valid policy tool for protecting domestic jobs and national security, but they are not the only metric that matters when evaluating economic outcomes. While efficiency is important, the social impact of tariffs—such as whether they truly help a community stay employed and secure—must be weighed alongside the costs to consumers and other sectors. A policy can be \"correct\" if it achieves its primary goal of protecting workers, even if it creates secondary inefficiencies or higher prices for some.",
